[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Adds a "Wooden stick" craft to the circular saw. Vanilla has no way to deliberately produce sticks, so early-game crafts that need a handful of them mean grinding fallen branches. This mod gives you a predictable supply.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Recipe[/b] — 1 Log → 12 Wooden sticks. Craftable at the circular saw.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Energy cost[/b] — 15 energy per craft.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]How to unlock[/b] — you need the circular saw itself, which is unlocked via the Carpentry I tech. Once the bench is built, the stick recipe appears in its craft menu.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue batches of the stick craft. Per-workbench auto-craft covers Carpentry, so the circular saw can run on its own.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — craft-output multiplier. One log can yield way more than 12 sticks if you want.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — halve the 15-energy cost, or make it zero with unlimited energy.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/51]Auto-Loot Heavies[/url] — teleports logs and timber to stockpiles for you.[/size]
[/list]

